For information, I’m connecting the limelight through PoE with a 12V 2A wall adapter and an ethernet cable connected to my computer. I’ve read other threads and this has been correctly done.

Any suggestions?

Thanks

Make sure that you’ve set up the network correctly Getting Started — Limelight 1.0 documentation

Additionally, you typically only connect through ethernet coming from your radio to your computer only during comp. If your radio is programmed to be able to connect to it already then it is more reliable to get the PoE and hook an ethernet from the orange cables ethernet port to your roborio and an ethernet from your limelight to your radios far right port then connecting to the roborio via wifi and then connecting to the limelight through 10.66.47.2 in the browser

Yes I had an Ethernet cable from the LL to my PC. In case you don’t know what it means to be on the same network: the IP address of the LL must match the IP address of the PC wherever the subnet mask has a bit one. The LL docs suggest 255.255.255.0 and that’s what I normally use and will work for the examples others have given here.

I hope I’m not leading you astray. There was some odd restriction using the LL but I don’t remember it being the roboRIO; I could be wrong and I don’t have a LL at home to try it. Sorry.

I believe the odd restriction I was thinking of is the LL won’t use a NetworkTables Server that isn’t on a real roboRIO. I had a NetworkTables server on my PC and named the PC the same as a roboRIO and used the IP address of a roboRIO but LL still wouldn’t use the NetworkTables server on it. I don’t remember this effecting the video streams. If they don’t show, try accessing them with their IP addresses which you have set and if they still don’t show, right click on where they should be and select Load Image (in Chrome).
